\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The stairs groaned softly, their creaks reverberating in the stillness of the apothecary.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton carefully mounted the steps. An attic was reached by a narrow wooden staircase. The polished railings sparkled under her fingertips. A small, circular window at the landing let soft light cast long shadows that danced with her every step.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 With each step, the town below faded into a whisper of bustling life. Replaced by the second floor\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s oppressive stillness. As she rose, her free hand gently caressed the coarse wooden walls. She touched the rough spots and gouges, scars from her son's growing.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As she approached the attic door, a moment of hesitation gripped her. Pausing for a brief moment, she lifted her hand with a touch of uncertainty. The wood stood strong, though it bore the marks of time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton closed her eyes, inhaled deeply, and then rapped softly with her knuckles, the sound a delicate, almost timid knock against the quietude.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Edward?\u8221\'94 she whispered into the quiet, her voice barely breaking the stillness of the attic. She leaned in.. The other side lingered in their silence. Her brow knitted together, a delicate line appearing between her eyes. She cast a fleeting look at the door handle, an urge to twist it, yet she held back.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Instead, she knocked again, this time with a deeper intent, the sound echoing more profoundly through the room beyond.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Silence. Thick and unmoving. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 -o-}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Beyond the attic door, the room lay in comfortable chaos. The space was dim, save for the slivers of morning light through his curtains. casting long, golden beams across the floor.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Clothes strewn carelessly across the floor, some draped over the back of a chair, some half-tucked under the bed, some long forgotten. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Books were }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 everywhere. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Its}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 stacked haphazardly on the desk, toppled over on the nightstand, spread open on the unmade bed as if abandoned mid-thought. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Loose parchment spilled onto the wooden floor, some pages crumpled, others torn at the edges. Half-sketched transmutation circles and scribbled formulas peeked out from beneath the clutter, most of them bore the chaotic scribbling of frustation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Its walls bore remnants of faded posters. Some curling at the edges, one hanging on by a single pin. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A calendar sat pinned to the wall near the door, its pages frozen in time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The last date marked in red ink from seven years ago.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 26th of April, 1920.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Near the farthest wall, a wooden desk was buried beneath the weight of research. Transmutation circles sketched and then discarded overflowed from a bin at the desk\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s side. Diagrams detailing herbs, plants and mushrooms. Their alchemical properties meticulously annotated in a careful yet restless hand. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Stacked books, their spines cracked from repeated use, bore names in gilded lettering\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 , }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Modern Alchemy}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  by Magnus Borman, and a vintage tome }{\f1\fs22\b0\i1 The Ancient Arts of Alchemy}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 signed only }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Catherine}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Amid the scholarly collection sat a battered notebook filled with translations of an even older text, one written by }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Casnius Bolos}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , one of the nine sages of enlightenment. The Father of Alchemy.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And slumped over it all, was the room\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s lone occupant.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 His maroon diamond-patterned sweater hung loosely over his slumped shoulders, its sleeves pushed up to his elbows. His silver hair fell messily over his forehead, unkempt from restless nights. His posture was hunched, arms folded beneath his head, his breathing slow and steady in slumber.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 In his ears, a pair of makeshift headphones\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 wired together in an unorthodox fashion\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 hummed faintly with a distant, crackling signal. Plugged into an even more makeshift radio, the device played something indiscernible, some half-lost frequency from far beyond Weshaven. Whether it was music or the muffled voices of a broadcast, only he could tell.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The knocking at the door continued. A soft, measured rhythm, persistent against the wood.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Still, he did not stir. Succumbing to his sleep and the sounds from distant lands.}
