\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 -o-}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She knocked again\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 more resolutely, as if the sound itself could unravel the silence that enveloped the room. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Eddie?\u8221\'94 She called, yet no answer. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton sighed, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course, I knew it\u8217\'92ll come to this.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Slipping her hand into her skirt pocket and touching her wand's smooth wooden surface. With a slight wrist movement, the wand appeared. A thin piece of dark oak with intricate interlocking ornaments. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She pointed it at the door's lock, and a gentle click rattled the quiet attic, flickering the runes around the lock before dissolving into the shadows. She tucked her wand away and gently opened the door. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The room was full of clutter.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s gaze swept the room, her eyebrows lifting slightly as she took in the disarray.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course,\u8221\'94 she muttered under her breath, stepping carefully over a crumpled tunic on the floor. \u8220\'93A storm couldn\u8217\'92t have done a better job.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She stared at the figure slumped on the desk, immovable except for his breathing breathing. Crackling of faint jazz music could be heard from the makeshift headset on the radio.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Edward Welton!\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 she yelled, her tone sharp but laced with exasperated fondness. }
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The name cut through the attic like a thunderclap.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie jolted awake so violently that his chair tipped backward. His arms flailed, his headset yanked free with a sharp crackle of static, and the makeshift radio tumbled off the desk with a clatter. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Books, parchments, loose papers exploded into the air, cascading down like confetti in a parade of overwork. His foot caught on something\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 maybe a discarded tunic, maybe an open book\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and he tumbled off his chair entirely, landing flat on his back with a heavy }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 thud}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 From the floor, he let out a groggy, half-incoherent groan. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Mum\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 what the hell?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton, unimpressed, loomed over him with her hands on her hips. "You agreed weeks ago to accompany Torrie on her first day of school! I'm not letting her get lost in Osthaven while you spend all morning hibernating like some bear in a cave!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She crossed the room with purpose, the floorboards thumping beneath her feet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie sat up, rubbing his silver hair, still blinking off the remnants of sleep. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Could you at least }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 knock}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  first?\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 he grumbled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "I }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 did}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  knock!" Mrs. Welton shot back, pointing at the unlocked door. "But you were too busy listening to\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 she gestured vaguely at the tangled mess of wires, the radio now buzzing with distorted, half-drowned static. \u8220\'93\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 whatever }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 that}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  is.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie picked up his fallen headset, giving the radio a once-over before dusting it off. "}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 It's called jazz}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , Mum," he said, as if that explained everything. "They're pretty famous in the city, you know?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Like I care about }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 that}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , Edward!" Mrs. Welton huffed. "Now }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 get up}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  before Torrie is late for her first day at Aella!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie groaned, rubbing the sleep from his eyes. "}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Aella}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ?" he muttered, his voice still thick with sleep. "}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Torrie\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  in Aella now?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton pinched the bridge of her nose. "}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 She is.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  Did you forget that }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 too}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Look, Mum," Eddie pushed himself up, wincing as he untangled his legs from a mess of books and crumpled clothes. "It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 difficult}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  to keep track of things when Dad\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s remedies need tweaking every two days." He stretched, his back popping as he tried to shake off the last bits of sleep. "}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Can I clean up a bit before we go?}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Welton bent down with a sigh, picking up the books and papers that had scattered across the floor. Unlike Eddie, who left things in precarious heaps, she stacked them neatly, smoothing out crumpled pages before placing them back onto his desk.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "You should at least }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 try}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  to keep things organized," she scolded, adjusting a pile of alchemy notes. "Honestly, Edward, I don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how you can work like this."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "I }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 do}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  work like this," Eddie shot back as he pulled a fresh shirt from a chair\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 though it was debatable how }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 fresh}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  it actually was. He gave it a quick sniff before pulling it on. "I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve been busy experimenting with potion ingredients for the apothecary. It\u8217\'92s not like I\u8217\'92m just }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 lounging}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  around."}}